<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> "At any rate, when <a href="/wiki/Cornelius_Gallus" title="Cornelius Gallus">Gallus</a> was prefect of Egypt, I accompanied him and ascended the <a href="/wiki/Nile" title="Nile">Nile</a> as far as <a href="/wiki/Aswan" title="Aswan">Syene</a> and the frontiers of <a href="/wiki/Kingdom_of_Aksum" title="Kingdom of Aksum" class="mw-redirect">Ethiopia</a>, and I learned that as many as one hundred and twenty vessels were sailing from <a href="/wiki/Myos_Hormos" title="Myos Hormos">Myos Hormos</a> to India, whereas formerly, under the <a href="/wiki/Ptolemaic_Egypt" title="Ptolemaic Egypt" class="mw-redirect">Ptolemies</a>, only a very few ventured to undertake the voyage and to carry on traffic in Indian merchandise." Strabo II.5.12. <a href="http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Strabo/2E1*.html" class="external text" title="http://penelope.uchicago.edu/Thayer/E/Roman/Texts/Strabo/2E1*.html" rel="nofollow">Source</a></li>
